  "prompt": "Does it hurt to get stitches removed?",
  "response": "The sensation of getting stitches removed can vary depending on the individual and the location of the stitches. Generally, most people experience minimal discomfort or a slight tugging sensation when stitches are being removed. However, it is usually not painful. If the area is still tender or healing, there might be some mild discomfort. If you are concerned about pain, you can discuss this with your healthcare provider, who can offer advice or take steps to minimize any discomfort during the procedure.",
